    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-06-08T19:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-06-08T19:25:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <head>40. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Iran</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d40fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, DEF 19–3 US–IRAN. Confidential. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_TMG1">Tiger</persName> and General <persName
                            corresp="#p_EMGGS1">Eckhardt</persName>, cleared by Colonel <persName
                            corresp="#p_TMD1">Taylor</persName> and Bartlett Harvey (<gloss
                            target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/PC), and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_TPH2">Talbot</persName>. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_CINCMEAFSA1">CINCMEAFSA</gloss>, and <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_CINCMEAFSA1">CINCMEAFSA</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_POLAD1"
                            >POLAD</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-06-08T20:25:00-04:00">June 8, 1964, 8:25 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>916. Joint State/<gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/Defense message. Military
                    modernization program discussed with Shah by <gloss target="#t_DOD1"
                    >DOD</gloss>, State and <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> reps on 6 June. Shah
                    was told <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> intends to be responsive to his
                    military modernization requirements. <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss> reps
                    suggested consideration Cooperative Logistics Sales Agreement. Regarding tanks,
                    Shah’s attention directed to M–48A3 as better priced substitute for M–60, which
                    now very high priced because of curtailed procurement schedule. Regarding
                    transport aircraft, we offered sale of four C–130’s on favorable credit terms
                    for delivery by July 1965. There was less concrete discussion concerning other
                    modernization items. Shah was pleased with general approach, requested further
                    meeting with working level <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss> on Monday, June
                    8, for more detailed discussion modernization plan, particularly possibilities
                    for reduction in price of M–60 as result possible procurement by Iran.</p>
                <p>At June 8 meeting, main emphasis was on tanks with Shah questioning sharply price
                    and characteristics data. Shah requested another meeting in New York on 12 June
                    at which time he would like to have firm information as to the availability of
                    the M–48A3 tank with the 105[mm] gun and, if possible, to discuss a draft
                    Cooperative Logistics Sales Agreement covering the entire modernization program.
                    Shah at no time asked for details about credit availability or terms but assumed
                    that this would be included in the discussion of a Cooperative Logistics Sales
                    Agreement.</p>
                <pb facs="0110" n="82" xml:id="pg_82"/>
                <p>Other subjects covered in meetings (<gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1"
                        >CINCSTRIKE</gloss> Air Defense Study, Iranian economic development) to be
                    covered in <gloss target="#t_memcon1">memcons</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
